                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/59.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Hostetter</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="104" xml:id="d1307fn104">Same to the Consular officers at Nogales and
                        Log Mochis.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reported to Department that Constitutionalists are threatening forced loan upon
                    Almacla Sugar Refineries Company, American corporation owning large properties
                    at Navolato near Culiacan.</p>
                <p>Make protest to Constitutionalist leaders against imposition of this loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
